04207nam a22008535i 9783110568059DE-B159720180327123002.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||180327s2018    gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831105680597 a10.1515/97831105680592doi  a(DE-B1597)488196  a(OCoLC)1029817493  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE10aP235 7aLAN0090002bisacsh 7aLAN0110002bisacsh00a4142231 aRecasens, Daniel,eauthor.14aThe Production of Consonant Clusters :bImplications for Phonology and Sound Change /cDaniel Recasens. 1aBerlin ;Boston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2018] 4cÂ©2018  a1 online resource (221 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aPhonology and Phonetics [PP] ;v2600tFrontmatter -- tTable of contents -- t1. Introduction -- t2. Production constraints and articulatory adaptation mechanisms -- t3. Homorganic clusters -- t4. Heterorganic articulators -- t5. Manner assimilation and weakening -- t6. Recapitulation and discussion -- tReferences -- tIndex of languages and dialects  aThe book analyzes the articulatory motivation of several adaptation processes (place assimilations, blending, coarticulation) involving consecutive consonants in heterosyllabic consonant sequences within the framework of the degree of articulatory constraint model of coarticulation. It also shows that the homorganic relationship between two heterosyllabic consonants contributes to the implementation of manner assimilations, while heterorganicity as well as sonorancy and voicing in the syllable-onset C2 are key factors in the weakening of the syllable-coda C1. Experimental and descriptive evidence is provided with production, phonological and sound change data from several languages, and more especifically with tongue-to-palate contact and lingual configuration data for Catalan consonant sequences. The book also reviews critically research on the c-center effect in tautosyllabic consonant sequences which has been carried out during the last thirty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Mrz 2018) 0aConsonants. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxPhonology. 0aPhonetics. 4aAssimilation. 4aConsonant Clusters. 4aElectropalatography. 4aUltrasound.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz978-3-11-056572-00 cprintz978311056567640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110568059423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110568059.jpg  a978-3-11-060407-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2018